<p>
    What’s possible in a week? If you dedicated seven days to the achievement of one goal,
    how ambitious could you make this goal? These were the questions that the multilingual
    twins Katy and Sara posed themselves when they determined to learn English in one week,
    to prove that it can be done and anyone can do it with the right methods.
</p>
<p>
    They would attempt to liberate themselves from the distractions and responsibilities of modern-day
    life in order to cram eight hours of study time and I was observing some of the world’s most capable
    language learners at work.
</p>

